	dprr:hasNoteText "Tr. Pl. 32. In MRR 2.418, refer also to Syme, Historia 13, 1964, 120; Wiseman, NM 245, no. 275.[147x]\n" .
<http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/PostAssertionNote/6477> rdfs:label "Post Assertion Note: #6477" ;
	a dprr:PostAssertionNote ;
	dprr:hasSecondarySourceForNote <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/SecondarySource/2> ;
	dprr:hasNoteType <http://romanrepublic.ac.uk/rdf/entity/NoteType/1> ;
	dprr:hasNoteText "The Consul Sosius was ready to propose immediate action against Octavian in the Senate on the first of February, but the Tribune interposed his veto (Dio 50.2.3, when Sosius had the fasces; see above, Consuls, on Sosius; and for the date ' T. Rice Holmes, Architect of the Roman Empire 234f.). See PIR 2.411, no. 101; De Laet no. 260." .
